         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>192</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>152</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>359</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5 #a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche in des Buddha (Śākyamu)ni Lehre Si(ttlichkeit bewahren), Gaben geben, mit Freude (das Wissen) lernen, den Sinn verstehen, ... auf den Wegen den Boden fegen, ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever], in the teaching of the Buddha (Śākyamu)ni, keep the moral conduct, give gifts, learn (the knowledge) with joy, understand the meaning, ..., sweep the ground on the paths, ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>359, 413</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>154</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>413</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>95</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...verehren sie Vater [und] Mutter.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... they venerate father [and] mother.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>143</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>191, 281</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3 #b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1988"/><citedRange>255</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>191</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>341</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>38</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>341</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>89</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>237</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... sitting on docile riding animals</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a276"/> (completing); MaitrHami 16, 13-15; MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 161, 162, 51</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment, which complements <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a276"/>, contains part of the sixteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka. Uy. parallels are MaitrHami 16, 13b20-15a2, and MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 161, 162, 51 (<bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>139-143</citedRange></bibl>). Immediately follows <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a286"/>+<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a260"/>. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>202-3</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="philcomment"><bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1993"/><citedRange>365f</citedRange></bibl>.[wrong!], <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1994c"/><citedRange>370f</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes A 251 - A 294 (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>).</note></p>
         </div>
